m;">Mathopolis:</span><a>Q1</a> <a>Q2</a> <a>Q3</a> <a>Q4</a> <a>Q5</a> <a>=
Q6</a> <a>Q7</a> <a>Q8</a> <a>Q9</a> <a>Q10</a> </div>
<div class=3D"gap"></div>

<div class=3D"center80">=20

<h3>Footnote: Geometry, Algebra and Sets</h3>=20

<p>You may not have noticed this ... but we have actually been using:</p>=
=20
<ul>=20
	<li><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/index.html">Algebra</a>,=
</li>=20
	<li><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/index.html">Geometry</a=
> (the Number Line is a <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/line=
.html">line</a>), and</li>=20
	<li><a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/sets/sets-introduction.html">Set=
s</a> (an interval is a set of numbers)</li>=20
</ul>=20
<p>all in one subject. Isn't mathematics amazing?</p>=20
</div>=20

